Exercise Part 3: Understanding Domain Model

The domain model relies on four main entity classes that serve as building blocks. The primary
entity is Task, which holds names, descriptions, and tags. To keep data safe, the app uses
type-safe TaskStatus and TaskPriority enums. It also utilizes a TaskStorage component that acts as
the file gatekeeper.The business logic focuses heavily on scheduling safeguards and strict
transitions.
Deadlines are validated against ISO date rules and set to LocalTime.MAX. Furthermore
when a task status shifts to TaskStatus.DONE, the engine runs task.markAsDone(). This method
securely stamps a permanent completion timestamp onto the data record.The codebase tracks "overdue
tasks" by filtering items past the current time. It also calculates a "completedRecently" metric to
measure a rolling 7-day productivity window.
Finally, it uses a unique "placeholder task" pattern
with a temporary title. This pattern lets the system safely patch single properties without
overwriting whole files.

